Feedback from IT







Ease of Use: Manage your settings, and find and connect with counterparties in seconds. Little to no training is required to start using Cloud9.


Global User Management: Access Cloud9’s self-service portal for global, centralized management of groups (trading desks) and users. Organizations can establish user profiles and policies across groups, subgroups, and at an individual level.







Voice Quality: Cloud9 features high definition audio, which means your counterparties will come in loud and clear and sound like they’re standing next to you.


Ease of Installation: Infrastructure and network service deployment and management are streamlined with a single, software-as-a-service based application that can be deployed on demand. Regardless of where a trader is located, implementation can be performed on site or remotely.







Expanded Network of Trading Parties: The Cloud9 directory organizes trading partners by communities and asset class, so it is easy to find and connect with new counterparties.


Service Updates: Software updates are automatically pushed to users, which means that users don’t have to worry about extensive cost and time associated with updating software and equipment.







Mobility: Work anywhere you have an internet connection, without being dependent on equipment and telcomm infrastructure.


Scalability: Software-as-a-service model means new users can be added or deleted based on business requirements.







Low Desktop Footprint: Takes up a small amount of space on an already crowded desktop.


Inherent Disaster Recovery: Eliminates the overhead associated with maintaining redundant equipment at a back-up disaster recovery site, while providing a more robust environment.



































